Sentencas: Preparation and electrochemical characterization of WO3-infiltrated 0.48W0.52CuScYSZ (WCS) anode for solid oxide fuel cell are reported.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The DC conductivity of a WO3 ceramic was 1,200 and 24?S?cm1 in reducing and oxidizing atmospheres, respectively, at 650?degrees C. WCS porous backbones in the form of symmetric cells were prepared by screen printing of WO3CuOScYSZ ink and subsequent sintering at 1,300?degrees C for 1?h in 9% H2/N2.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Analysis of the sintered backbone by X-ray diffraction showed the metallic W and Cu phases.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Precursor solutions of WO3 or CuO were infiltrated into porous WCS backbones to form the anode.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of these anodes measured by impedance spectroscopy showed polarization resistances of 11 and 6.5?Omega?cm2 for WO3 and CuO infiltrated anodes, respectively, at 600?degrees C in humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Activation energy values of 86.8 and 96.5?kJ?mol1 were obtained for WO3 and CuO infiltrated WCS anodes, respectively.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The microstructure of the tested anodes showed well-dispersed sub-micron particles of WO3 in the WCS backbone whereas CuO infiltration resulted in a dense microstructure.
Titulo: A Preliminary Study on WO3-Infiltrated W-Cu-ScYSZ Anodes for Low Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
